text: Hurricane Francine was a moderate Atlantic tropical cyclone in September 2024. The storm struck south central Louisiana as a category 2 hurricane. Winds were 100 miles per hour or more. The state of Mississippi was also affected by the storm when Francine cut through the area. Damage from Francine was almost $1.5 billion. No people, however, were killed. ==References== Category:Hurricanes in the United States Category:2024 in weather Category:Hurricanes in Mississippi
title: Hurricane Francine
